<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Chicken Note</div>
<div class="nbunit" id="udn63"> See in this general connection Michael Seidel <cite>Epic Geography: James Joyce&apos;s Ulysses</cite> (Princeton: Princeton University Press, 1976); Danis Rose and John O&apos;Hanlon, <cite>The Lost Notebook</cite> (Split Pea Press, Edinburgh, 1989); and Michael Groden, <cite>Ulysses in Progress</cite> (Princeton: Princeton University Press, 1977). Another interesting book is Victor B&eacute;rard&apos;s <cite>Did Homer Live?</cite>, translated by Brian Rhys and published (London and Toronto) in 1931. I have made much use of this.  </div>
